-- Polish Stocks: CEDC, Hydrobudowa, PBG, Rafako Active in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i   a n d   M a r t a   W a l d o c h
-- 2012-06-05T15:52:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-05/polish-stocks-cedc-hydrobudowa-pbg-rafako-active-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  slipped 1.8
percent to 2,039.72 at the close in Warsaw.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Central European Distribution Corp. (CDC)  , nation’s
second-largest vodka producer, dropped 15 percent to 11.2 zloty,
the lowest since Nov. 25, after saying it may need to restate
financial results for 2010 and 2011.  PBG SA (PBG)  , the country’s third-largest builder,
tumbled 46 percent to 7.86 zloty, and its  Hydrobudowa Polska SA (HBP) 
 unit lost 38 percent to 0.21 zloty, falling the most
since their debuts on the Warsaw Stock Exchange after both
companies filed for bankruptcy yesterday.  Rafako SA (RFK)  ,
the power engineering unit of PBG, fell 2.8 percent to 5.91
zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
